<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Oil Well </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Turkish villagers discover oil after earthquake
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ADANA, Turkey (AP) _ Villagers returning to their fields after a
deadly earthquake discovered oil oozing out of a water well,
officials said Tuesday.
	   They dug the well a day before a magnitude-6.3 quake struck this
southern region, Adana Gov. Oguz Kaan Koksoz told ATV television.
	   ``All they got at first was dirty water,'' Koksoz said. ``When
they came back, there was oil.''
	   Officials from the state-owned pipeline company, Botas, were
dispatched to the village of Soysali to inspect the well.
	   ``We are hoping that the reserve is quite a large one,'' said
Botas official Fatih Sen.
	   Although surrounded by a number of countries with large oil
resources, Turkey is poor in petroleum.
	   The June 27 quake killed 140 people and injured more than 1,000.
	   (sf-cph)
</TEXT>
