<HEADLINE>
Moldova to pay Gazprom debt
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KISHINEV, Moldova (AP) _ Moldova will pay its dlrs 215 million
debt to the Russian gas monopoly by selling bonds and handing over
some of the country's gas assets, the government said Tuesday.
	   Moldova is prepared to set up a joint venture between its gas
assets and Gazprom, Deputy Prime Minister Ion Sturza said at a news
conference. Gazprom would have a 50-percent stake in the venture
worth about dlrs 100 million, he said.
	   ``It is possible that we would issue dlrs 90 million bonds for
ten years and pass them to Gazprom also,'' Sturza said.
	   Gazprom slashed gas exports to Moldova in half on July 1 because
of the debts and threatened to cut supplies Aug. 1.
	   Of Moldova's debt, dlrs 75 million are penalties and Sturza said
those might be pardoned.
	   Moldova's breakaway Trans-Dniester region owes about dlrs 400
million to Gazprom but that debt is being negotiated separately.
	   (str/mc/ls) 	   
