<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Fires </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fires kill more than 150 in Moscow this year
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Fires have killed 156 people in Moscow so far this
year, a news agency reported Tuesday.
	   The 9,500 fires in the Russian capital also caused 8 million
rubles (dlrs 1.3 million) in damages, ITAR-Tass said, quoting the
city's firefighting administration.
	   The report said that 36.9 percent of the fires were started by
smokers.
