<SLUG> BC-Guyana-Lost Ranger,0176 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Lost ranger returns home after 10-day ordeal in rain forest
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   GEORGETOWN, Guyana (AP) _ A forest ranger lost in the Guyanese
jungle for 10 days returned home this week, bruised and
mosquito-bitten but otherwise in good health.
	   Raymond Houston, 51, disappeared July 4 while helping teen
volunteers work on a Guyana Forestry Commission station about 90
miles (140 kilometers) southwest of Georgetown.
	   Houston, a 20-year veteran of the forestry commission, had gone
into the bush to find some students he thought were lost. He lost
his bearings in heavy rain.
	   Fighting off fatigue and mosquitoes, he hiked for days through
swamps filled with caimans and poisonous snakes. ``Once, I was so
tired I slept in a swamp holding on to a tree,'' Houston said. ``I
prayed a lot and asked God for sustenance.''
	   He stumbled out of the jungle Wednesday at a logging camp 20
miles away. He was treated for dehydration and hundreds of insect
bites before being brought home on Sunday.
</TEXT>
