<HEADLINE>
Former Cabinet member says Botha ordered bombing
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: RECASTS lead to emphasize Vlok's statement an allegation.
CORRECTS slug &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos JOH101-102 &QL; 
 &UR; By PAT REBER &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   PRETORIA, South Africa (AP) _ After years of conjecture about
apartheid's chain of command, a former Cabinet minister on Tuesday
detailed how former President P.W. Botha allegedly ordered the
destruction of a church headquarters.
	   Adriaan Vlok, graf 2 pvs
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-South Africa-Botha-Bombing, 3rd Ld; CT:i; 
(REG:EURO;)
(REG:BRIT;)
(REG:SCAN;)
(REG:MEST;)
