<HEADLINE>
Puppy in Canada needs US dlrs 871 surgery on smashed leg after
</HEADLINE>
beating

<TEXT>
	   CHATHAM, Ontario (AP) _ A Canadian youth has been charged after
a puppy was beaten so badly it needed dlrs 1,300 (US dlrs 871) of
surgery to repair its smashed leg.
	   A veterinarian had to pin one of the dog's hind legs together
after someone repeatedly kicked the six-month-old dog about three
weeks ago.
	   Cathy Crawford, a spokeswoman at the Ontario Society of the
Prevention of Cruelty to Animals, said the number of animal abuse
cases are on the rise.
	   In 1997, there were 272 cases of neglect and abuse reported in
the Chatham area, up from 253 in 1996.
	   A new home is being sought for the dog.
	   The youth, who cannot be identified under provisions of the
Young Offenders Act, could be fined up to dlrs 2,000 (US dlrs 1300)
and spend six months in jail if found guilty.
</TEXT>
