<SLUG> BC-Jamaica-Parliaments,0159 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
``New creative thinking'' needed in parliaments, Jamaica PM says
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KINGSTON, Jamaica (AP) _ Lawmakers need ``new creative
thinking'' to handle increasing international cooperation and
global business, Jamaican Prime Minister P.J. Patterson told a
conference of parliamentarians Tuesday.
	   Speaking at the 23rd regional conference of the Commonwealth
Parliamentary Association in Kingston, Patterson said
multi-national businesses were pushing governments to lower
tariffs, change quotas and alter exchange controls to eliminate
boundaries between countries.
	   Lawmakers will be challenged to find solutions that can retain
sovereign powers, he said.
	   ``It cannot be business as usual. It cannot be legislation as
usual,'' he said. ``There is now a compelling need for new creative
thinking. The new world order will render us obsolete unless we
prove ourselves adequate to the task.''
</TEXT>
