	   WORLD SPORTS AT 0000 GMT
 &UR; SOCCER:
	   LONDON _ Barely 10 days after the World Cup final, the new
soccer season gets going in Europe Wednesday with the first
qualifying round of the Champions and UEFA Cup competitions.
	   Slug-Sports-Soccer-European Preview. Has moved.
	   By Robert Millward
	   ROME _ Italy's coaching carousel continues to spin, with Cesare
Maldini officially out as head of the national soccer team, the
federation announces Tuesday.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-Italy Coach. Has moved.
	   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil _ Nine days after Brazil's loss to France
in the World Cup finals, speculation about what happened to star
forward Ronaldo continued to be a hot topic in the Brazilian press
Tuesday.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-Ronaldo Mystery. Has moved.
 &UR; AUTO RACING:
	   LONDON _ Reigning Formula One champion Jacques Villeneuve is set
to quit Williams and join the new British American Racing team for
next season, BBC radio reports.
	   Slug Sports-Auto Racing-Villeneuve. Has moved.
 &UR; GOLF:
	   LONDON _ A 10-handicap golfer, Martin Holmes is unlikely to find
his name on the claret jug that goes to the winner of the British
Open. Yet he believes it should be there alongside Mark O'Meara's.
	   Slug Sports-Golf-O'Meara's Lost Ball. Has moved.
	   By Robert Millward
	   SOUTHPORT, England _ First, it was Matt Kuchar at the Masters
and U.S. Open. Then it was Justin Rose and Sergio Garcia at the
British Open. Amateurs seem at home at the majors this year.
	   Slug Spotrs-Golf-Amateur Year. Has moved.
	   By Doug Ferguson.
