	   _ SOUTHPORT, England _ Sports-Golf-Notes. By Doug Ferguson. Has
moved.
	   _ HILVERSUM, Netherlands _ Sports-Golf-Rose. Has moved.
	   LOS ANGELES _ John Bland, who finished second behind Graham
Marsh in the 1997 U.S. Senior Open, withdraws from this year's
competition on Tuesday because his wife is ill.
	   Slug Sports-Golf-Senior Open. Has moved.
	   By John Nadel.
 &UR; CYCLING:
	   PARIS _ The doping scandal overshadowing the Tour de France
takes another turn with the lawyer for the Festina team doctor
claiming riders were ordered to contribute to a fund used to buy
illegal substances that enhance cycling performances.
	   Slug-Sports-Cycling-Doping. Has moved.
	   by Andreas Evagora
	   LUCHON, France - Defending champion Jan Ullrich regains the
overall lead in the Tour de France by leading an attack up the
final climb.
	   Slug-Sports-Cycling-Tour de France. Has moved.
	   by Salvatore Zanca
	   With:
	   _ LUCHON, France _ Sports-Cycling-Tour de France-Glance. Has
moved.
 &UR; TENNIS:
	   STUTTGART, Germany _ Spain's Galo Blanco needs three sets to
oust 18-year-old Russian Marat Safin Monday on the first day of the
Mercedes Cup.
	   Slug Sports-Tennis-Mercedes Cup. Has moved.
	   Also:
	   _ WASHINGTON _ Sports-Tennis-Legg Mason. Expected by 0200 GMT.
 &UR; BASKETBALL:
	   NEW YORK _ Finally, a hint of progress. NBA commissioner David
Stern and players' union director Billy Hunter meet for 90 minutes
and agree to resume labor talks.
	   Slug Sports-Basketball-NBA Lockout. Has moved.
