<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-El Salvador-Nuns, 3rd Add,0121 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador: prison disturbance.
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   The guardsmen were sentenced to 30 years in prison in May 1984
and have been jailed since 1981. They were to be given credit for
time served before their convictions.
	   The U.S. State Department criticized the decision to order the
release of three national guardsmen when it was first announced in
June. The releases have been held up by appeals by prosecutors.
	   The guardsmen have claimed in recent interviews that
``higher-ups'' ordered the killing of the four American church
workers.
	   The national guard was disbanded after a 1992 peace agreement
ended the civil war, which killed an estimated 75,000 people.
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-El Salvador-Nuns, 3rd Add; CT:i; 
(REG:EURO;)
(REG:BRIT;)
(REG:SCAN;)
(REG:ENGL;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
