<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Legg Mason,0195 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Storm postpones tennis tournament
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WASHINGTON (AP) _ A heavy thunderstorm derailed the ATP Tour
comeback of Jimmy Arias on Tuesday and left the Legg Mason Classic
in the dark.
	   Arias, 34 next month, led Wade McGuire 6-4, 2-5 when the storm
struck. The Fitzgerald Tennis Center and the surrounding 30-block
area was left without power.
	   The outage delayed or postponed 14 of the 19 matches scheduled
Tuesday, including second-seeded Andre Agassi's second-round match.
	   Tournament officials added a session Wednesday morning to make
up the matches. But Agassi was not scheduled to play until the
regular late afternoon session Wednesday. That session will also
feature a match involving top-seeded Michael Chang.
	   Arias, playing in his first tour match since 1994, breezed in
the first set Tuesday despite a temperature on the court of 112
degrees Fahrenheit (44 degress Celsius). But he was about to lose
the second set when the fast-moving storm blew in.
	   The only seed to finish play Tuesday, ninth-seeded Jeff Turango,
advanced with a 6-1, 6-2 victory over Johan Van Herck of Belgium.
</TEXT>
