<HEADLINE>
Australia's Packer en route to United States for surgery: report
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) _ Australian media baron Kerry Packer
plans to fly to the Cornell Medical Center in New York for heart
surgery, a local media report said Wednesday.
	   Packer, who has been a patient at Sydney's Royal Prince Alfred
Hospital for more than a week, will be accompanied Wednesday by a
team of medical staff, the Sydney Morning Herald newspaper
reported.
	   The report said Packer, Australia's richest man, was believed to
have already undergone an operation in which his main kidney artery
was unblocked with a balloon.
	   If the kidney procedure proved successful, he will not need to
continue dialysis, it said. But if not, Packer will need a renal
transplant with a family member likely to provide a kidney. 	   
