<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Do Nothing Generals </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Thai Defense Ministry: too many generals with too little to do
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Thailand's military has become
top-heavy as nearly 700 of the country's 2,646 generals have little
daily work to keep them busy, a local media report said Wednesday.
	   As a result, Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai, who is also the
country's first civilian defense minister in more than 20 years, is
limiting promotions to the rank of general, the Bangkok Post
reported Wednesday.
	   The paper cited a Defense Ministry report which said 689
generals lacked specific assignments. They were all attached to the
offices of the Supreme Command and army, navy and air force
headquarters.
	   In addition, 1,009 of the military's 3,098 colonels also have no
specific job assignments.
	   Thailand's military has approximately 275,000 men, and is one of
the better equipped armed forces in Southeast Asia. 	   
</TEXT>
